chunk_content: To review a repository of country-specific guidance and polices related to HIV self-testing, please visit the HIV Self-Testing Research and Policy Hub. How to review for Data should be reviewed regularly for the purposes of program management, to monitor progress data quality: towards achieving targets, and to identify and correct any data quality issues. For example, the number of test kits distributed should not be greater than the number of test kits a provider was 103 allocated during the reporting period. Careful attention is required regarding the number of HIVST kits distributed through pharmacies and online platforms. T Implementing partners should review their data to ensure that HTS_SELF is not reported under E S HTS_TST (or HTS_TST_POS) results. Furthermore, data should be reviewed to ensure the numerator T does not include the number of HIV self-tests performed or used, nor a definitive diagnosis (rapid HIV I N diagnostic tests should be reported under HTS_TST).
